fields.creole: wen taim kom fu slaata yu doz ga fu kyerii it rait de, an den dem a dedokt fu dem, an den yu a get wan smaal ting
fields.english: When the time came for slaughtering, you would have had to carry it right there, and then they would have deducted for themselves, and then you would have got a small payment.

fields.creole: wii jes chap dem wid di kotlas, an wii pik op som keen liif, an jes roos dem kliin, an wii divaid am bitwiin wii paatna, tek a piis, iit, and kom hoom
fields.english: We just chop them with our cutlasses, and we collect some (sugar}-cane leaves, and just roast them cleanly. And we divide it with our partner, take a piece, eat, and return horne.

fields.creole: nau di chap push an ai push, an hii hool a piis a mangoo an ai hool a piis a di mangoo. weI, at a sudn, ai get straanga dan di maan. su wen ai pul di ting,  di chap let goo di mangoo. an wen hii let goo di man goo ai faal aan di kotlas an mi hool said oopn
fields.english: Now the chap pushed and I pushed, and he held a piece of the mango and I held a piece of the mango. Well, suddenly, I got stronger than the man. So when I pulled the thing, the chap let go of the mango. And when he let go of the mango I fell on the cutlass and split my side.
